<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANKLE INJURY TO SIDELINE CASSIDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Cassidy, a senior starting guard for St. Genevieve High, said that he will 
miss Friday's San Fernando Valley League game against Notre Dame because of a 
sprained left ankle. 
</P>
<P>
Cassidy, who leads Valley-area players in assists with an 11.4 average, was 
injured Tuesday during the Valiants' 71-47 loss to Bell-Jeff. 
</P>
<P>
"It's not broken and I don't think I tore anything," Cassidy said. "It's just 
sprained pretty good. I'm on crutches." 
</P>
<P>
Cassidy, who averages a team-high 15.6 points a game, said that he will attempt 
to return for Tuesday's game against Harvard. 
</P>
