<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mitek Systems, a manufacturer of high-security computer printers and facsimile 
machines, reported a loss of $242,000 on sales of $3.9 million for the first 
quarter ended Dec. 31, against a loss of $612,000 on sales of $1.5 million over 
the same quarter the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
The company blamed the loss mainly on "one-time expenses associated with new 
products that have recently begun shipping." 
</P>
</TEXT>
