<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oak Industries has signed a letter of intent to purchase all of Orlando-based 
Chip Supply Inc.'s issued and outstanding shares for an unspecified amount of 
cash and common stock, Oak Chairman E. L. McNeely said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The purchase marked "a continuance of our strategic plan to acquire companies 
that complement our existing businesses," McNeely said. 
</P>
<P>
Chip Supply manufactures monolithic integrated circuit chips for the aerospace 
and space satellite market. The company reported $4 million in operating income 
on $20 million in revenue for the year ended Dec. 31. Chip Supply will continue 
to operate in its existing headquarters and factory in Orlando. 
</P>
</TEXT>
