<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A tape of an interview convicted murderer Ted Bundy had with Christian 
anti-pornography crusader Dr. James Dobson shortly before his execution last 
week will be offered to the public in exchange for a donation of under $30. On 
the 29-minute videotaped, Bundy blames pornography for helping to turn him into 
a serial killer. An executive with Dobson's Focus on the Family organization 
said the videotape would be put "in the hands of people with anti-pornography 
groups . . . (to( meet whatever demand is there." Internal Revenue Service 
regulations prevent direct sale of the videotape by the ministry. ALEENE 
MacMINN 
</P>
