<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLANNED PARENTHOOD SETS GOURMET FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Planned Parenthood Guild, a nonprofit volunteer organization 
dedicated to providing reproductive health care and education, will present its 
annual gala gourmet event, Fantasy Food Fare 1989, at the Riviera Country Club, 
1250 Capri Drive, Pacific Palisades, Feb. 9. 
</P>
<P>
Participants include some of the city's best chefs and restaurateurs, boutique 
owners, party planners, caterers, florists, food specialists, wineries, table 
setting designers and entertainers. 
</P>
<P>
Daytime festivities take place from 10:30 a.m. to 3 p.m. and include a 
marketplace, an unusual collection of food and gift items for the home. Some of 
the unique food items that guests can purchase include guava jellies, jams, 
sauces, dessert breads, cookies and chutneys. A raffle, food and wine tastings 
and a silent auction, in which participants bid on such items as antique 
jewelry and restaurant gift certificates, also will be held. 
</P>
<P>
Evening events, slated from 6 to 10 p.m., feature a mini-supper, wine tasting 
and cabaret featuring live music, dancing and fortune telling by Tommie 
Shulman. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets at $80 are for entry to both daytime and evening events. Tickets for 
daytime events are $55. All tickets will be held at the door and free parking 
is available at the club. 
</P>
<P>
Music and entertainment will be provided by Bruce Campbell Music, Inc.; 
Casanova Robots, the Party Machines; caricaturist Kris Vincencio; the Good 
Gypsy: Ziguener Verdad; and Zavier. 
</P>
<P>
All proceeds from the food fare, the raffle and the silent auction, and 25% of 
all other sales, will benefit Planned Parenthood. 
</P>
