43 DIE IN PHILIPPINE CLASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philippine troops backed by helicopter gunships battled Muslim rebels in a 
southern province, and 43 people were killed, the military said Wednesday. The 
dead in Tuesday's battle in Zamboanga del Sur province, about 500 miles 
southeast of Manila, included 32 guerrillas, eight civilians, two militiamen 
and one soldier. 
</P>
