<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fourth man convicted of raping a woman in Balboa Park last summer was 
sentenced to seven years in state prison Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Three other men had received the same sentence as Michael DeLeon, 20. All four 
were undocumented aliens. 
</P>
<P>
The rape of the 22-year-old Santee woman occurred at 6:30 a.m. Aug. 22. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Municipal Judge Robert Stahl also imposed a $100 fine on DeLeon, as 
he did on the three others. They are Gabriel Gutierrez, 22; Jose DeJesus 
Hernandez Leyva, 24, and Manuel Ponce Renteria, 20. Three others accused in the 
case are juveniles and have been prosecuted in Juvenile Court. 
</P>
<P>
The adults pleaded guilty to performing a rape in concert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
