<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego woman, hospitalized Sunday afternoon with a head wound after 
allegedly being shot by her son-in-law, died early Wednesday morning, a deputy 
coroner said. 
</P>
<P>
Audrey Erbe, 58, died at Sharp Memorial Hospital at 1:30 a.m. A bullet had 
lodged in her brain and she had not been expected to survive, a hospital 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested in connection with the shooting was Randy Ernest Geering, 36, who 
reportedly quarreled with his mother-in-law and his estranged wife after 
confronting them in the women's restroom of a doughnut shop in the 5000 block 
of Balboa Avenue in Clairemont. 
</P>
<P>
After the shooting, Geering fled to his wife's apartment in the 5500 block of 
Balboa Arms Drive, where he called a television station, reportedly to confess 
the shooting. The station called police, who arrested Geering. 
</P>
<P>
The district attorney's office plans to change a charge of attempted murder to 
murder during Geering's bail review on Friday, said Gregg McClain, a deputy 
district attorney. Geering is being held in County Jail in lieu of $200,000 
bail. 
</P>
