<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
STUDENTS WIN ESSAY CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four students won free trips to Spain in an essay contest to commemorate 
Spain's participation in the festivities marking the 75th anniversary of the 
city of Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Students were asked to write essays on the "significance of our Spanish 
heritage." A total of 149 students competed. 
</P>
<P>
Winners were Nancy Rennett, a third-grader; Justin Brooks, a fifth-grader; Sara 
Myers, a seventh-grader, and Samantha Weinstein, an 11th-grader. 
</P>
<P>
Each winner received three round-trip tickets to Madrid on Iberia Airlines, 
which co-sponsored the contest with the Spanish Consulate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
