<P>
Photo, Courtly Splendor of Chinese Artistry Colorful and majestic Chinese 
artistry, primarily from the Ch'ing Dynasty (1644-1911), are dazzling visitors 
to an exhibit at Lang Gallery at Scripps College in Claremont. The exhibit, 
which will run through Feb. 12, includes an 80th-birthday greeting in the form 
20-by-12-foot tapestry, delivered in 1779; a pair of four-inch embroidered 
shoes for the bound feet of women, and a civil dignitary hat and horsehair 
whisks, viewed by Ginny Nishigaya. The exhibition was organized from the 
permanent collections of the Claremont Colleges by students at Pitzer, Pomona 
and Scripps colleges. LOU MACK / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
