<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 INCUMBENTS AMONG 14 IN RUNNING FOR 3 COUNCIL SEATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fourteen candidates met Tuesday's filing deadline for Glendale City Council 
elections, and they will be on the ballot on April 4. 
</P>
<P>
The field of candidates running for three seats on the five-member council 
includes two incumbents -- Mayor Carl W. Raggio and Councilwoman Ginger 
Bremberg. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman John F. Day will not seek a fourth term on the council. His 
announced retirement opened the gates for the largest field of candidates in at 
least three decades. 
</P>
<P>
Also running are Robin Westmiller, the owner of a speakers bureau; attorney 
Shirley Yap Griffin; architect Richard Diradourian; laboratory technician Gary 
L. Siglar; attorney Nida Solana Brown; real estate broker S. Joe Ayvazi; 
Richard N. (Dick) Williams, a Carnation Co. vice president; retired sheriff's 
deputy P. E. (Ed) Dorris; Richard Navarro, a Glendale police officer; Richard 
Seeley, a gardener and landscaper; public relations executive Berdj P. 
Karapetian; and publisher Richard Jutras. 
</P>
<P>
To run for the council, each candidate was required to submit 500 signatures of 
supporters registered as Glendale voters, and pay $400 in fees. 
</P>
