<HEADLINE>
<P>
49ER WOMEN CAGERS TO PLAY HOST TO SAN JOSE STATE TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Long Beach women's basketball team will play San Jose State at 
7:30 tonight in the university gym. 
</P>
<P>
Coming off an 85-81 victory at Nevada-Las Vegas on Monday night, the 49ers have 
won seven games in a row. They are 14-4 overall and 8-0 in the Big West 
Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Penny Toler leads the 49ers with an 18.2-point average, followed by Traci 
Waites, averaging 17.7, and Shameil Coleman, averaging 11.4. 
</P>
<P>
The 49ers are averaging 95 points a game in the league. 
</P>
<P>
San Jose is 3-14 overall, 0-8 in the Big West and has lost seven straight. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach will play another home game Saturday night against Fresno State. 
</P>
