<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS LONG BEACH TO PLAY UTAH STATE IN BIG WEST GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DICK WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Long Beach basketball team will play Utah State in a battle for 
fourth place in the Big West Conference tonight at Logan, Utah. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach is 8-10 overall and Utah State is 7-12, but each is 5-4 in the 
conference. 
</P>
<P>
The 49ers are led by center John Hatten, who, coming off a career-high 37 
points against UC Irvine, has averaged 20 in conference games. 
</P>
<P>
Reid Newey is Utah State's leading scorer, averaging 20.4 points. DICK WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020289-0140 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 13294 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 2, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
