<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
EL TORO ALLOWS 1 POINT IN 1ST HALF, BEATS SAN CLEMENTE, 62-33 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Toro High School scored the first 22 points and held San Clemente to 1 point 
in the first half of a 62-33 South Coast League basketball victory Wednesday at 
El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers (13-9, 3-4) led, 12-0, at the end of the first quarter and 22-0 
midway through the second quarter before Eddie Morgan made a free throw. El 
Toro led, 28-1, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Rob Johnson scored 19 points and Greg Everett 12 for El Toro. Jason Dunahee 
scored 12 points for San Clemente (4-15, 1-6). 
</P>
<P>
In other South Coast League games: 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 74, Mission Viejo 50 -- Chris Kostoff scored 20 points and 
Scott McCorkle 19 to lead the host Cougars (17-4, 7-0). Capistrano Valley led, 
24-12, after the first quarter and 38-21 at halftime. Eric Cramer scored 15 
points for Mission Viejo (8-12, 3-4). 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 53, Dana Hills 38 -- Bryan Allred scored 20 points to lead Irvine (20-3, 
6-1) at Dana Hills. Kevin O'Neill scored 12 points for Dana Hills (13-11, 1-6). 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 88, Katella 59 -- Matt Luke had 13 points and 24 rebounds to lead 
visiting El Dorado, the league's first-place team. El Dorado, which has won 11 
in a row, led, 44-24, at halftime. Mike Bradach had 21 points and Jeff Cardenas 
17 for El Dorado (17-4, 7-0). Brian Yourstone had 20 to lead Katella (6-13, 
2-5). 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 76, Loara 58 -- Tes Whitlock of Loara had a game-high 29 points, 
but it wasn't enough. Los Alamitos outscored Loara, 32-12, in the fourth 
quarter. Robert Conlisk 16 points and Todd Chesebro 14 for Los Alamitos (10-12, 
5-2). Loara is 4-14, 2-5. 
</P>
