Esperanza 68, Cypress 64 -- Moose Pope and Joe Foss each scored 17 points to 
lead Esperanza (7-14, 1-6) to its first league victory. Mark Johnson scored 25 
points for Cypress (9-12, 4-3). 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 76, Troy 63 -- Curtis Morris scored 22 points and Pete Bach 19 to 
lead Fullerton 14-5, 7-0) at Troy. The Indians led, 32-30, at halftime and 
outscored the Warriors, 21-15, in the third quarter to take a 53-45 lead. 
Richard Wesley scored 19 points and John Lowe 13 for Troy (5-14, 1-6). 
</P>
<P>
La Habra 63, Buena Park 52 -- Tim Moore scored 18 points and David Stevens 16 
to lead host La Habra (11-9, 5-2). The victory clinches a playoff spot for La 
Habra for the first time in five seasons. The Highlanders are in third place, 
three games ahead of fourth-place Sonora with three games remaining. La Habra 
has defeated the Raiders twice this season. Richard Harvey scored 15 points for 
Buena Park (0-16, 0-7). 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 76, Sonora 51 -- Brett Mitchelson had a game-high 20 points to lead 
visiting Sunny Hills. Walter Mitter added 13 points and Marcus Hopkins 12 for 
Sunny Hills (14-7, 6-1). Greg Farlow had 16 points for Sonora (7-13, 2-5). 
</P>
<P>
Edison 64, Fountain Valley 58 -- Bill Martineau scored a game-high 20 points to 
lead Edison (11-12, 4-3) at Fountain Valley. Fountain Valley (16-5, 4-3) had an 
off night shooting, making just 20 of 61 shots from the floor for 33%. Tom 
Weaver led Fountain Valley with 15 points and Mike Merli added 14. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 65, Marina 61 -- Andy Thompson scored 22 points, including 2 
free throws in the last minute, for Huntington Beach (11-9, 6-1) at Marina. 
Cherokee Parks had 20 points and 11 rebounds for Marina (9-13, 2-5). 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 64, Westminster 51 -- Todd Norman had 18 points and Mike Frohn 14 
for visiting Ocean View. The Seahawks (15-6, 5-2) led, 18-9, at the end of the 
first quarter and gradually pulled away. Tim Dietel had 17 to lead Westminster 
(3-16, 0-7). 
</P>
